FBIS4-15712 "drsov069_b_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 9 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Kostikov Cites Plans To Change Government Policy Kostikov Cites Plans To Change Government Policy MK0904104094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 9 Apr 94 p 1 MK0904104094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Unattributed INTERFAX report in the "In Brief" column: "The Government Policy Will Change"] [Text] Boris Yeltsin is serious about the mounting criticism of the government's performance and, in coordination with Viktor Chernomyrdin, will apparently introduce some adjustments into the cabinet's activity. This was announced 8 April by presidential press secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov. In particular, according to him, adjustments are possible in the sphere of tax and customs policy. Mr. Kostikov stressed that the president and the prime minister have a good relationship and bear "no grudge against each other."
